<!-- Build artifacts and intermediate files: For example, if you're building a Go application, you might want to exclude the bin and pkg directories.

Version control system directories: For example, if you're using Git, you might want to exclude the .git directory.

Temporary files and directories: For example, you might want to exclude a tmp directory or files with the .log or .swp extensions.

Large files or directories that are not needed at runtime: For example, you might want to exclude a large_files directory that contains data files that are only needed for development or testing.

Here's an example .dockerignore file that excludes some common items:

# ignore all files in the .git directory
.git/

# ignore all files in the build/ directory
build/

# ignore all .log files
*.log -->
.git/